<div class="text-center mt-2 mb-4">
  Designed and modeled a single-story commercial fitness center in Autodesk Revit 2026, encompassing full architectural and mechanical systems for a 3,984 SF facility located in Chicago, Illinois. Engineering calculations were developed referencing ASHRAE 62.1 and 90.1 standards, and clash detection was performed in Navisworks Manage.
</div>

<!-- Architectural Design -->
<h4 class="text-center mt-5">Architectural Design</h4>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-4">
  <div class="col-sm-6 mb-3">
    {% include figure.liquid loading="eager" path="assets/projectimages/Fitness Center/L1 - Architectural.png" title="Architectural Floor Plan" alt="Architectural Floor Plan" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" zoomable=true style="height: 300px; object-fit: contain;" %}
  </div>
</div>
<div class="text-center mt-2 mb-4">
  Developed a complete architectural floor plan including a training area, men's and women's locker rooms, reception, office, and mechanical room. Applied finish materials and equipment families throughout the model including gym equipment, locker room fixtures, and office furniture.
</div>

<!-- HVAC System Design -->
<h4 class="text-center mt-5">HVAC System Design</h4>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-4">
  <div class="col-sm-6 mb-3">
    {% include figure.liquid loading="eager" path="assets/projectimages/Fitness Center/L2 - Mechanical.png" title="Mechanical Floor Plan" alt="Mechanical Floor Plan" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" zoomable=true style="height: 300px; object-fit: contain;" %}
  </div>
</div>
<div class="text-center mt-2 mb-4">
  Designed a complete HVAC system serving six zones including an air handling unit, supply ductwork, return ductwork, locker room exhaust system, and outdoor air intake. Supply diffusers, return grilles, and exhaust grilles were sized using ACH-based CFM calculations with duct velocities verified against ASHRAE limits of 1,500 FPM for supply and 1,200 FPM for return. Outdoor air intake was sized to meet ASHRAE 62.1 minimum ventilation requirements of 1,034 CFM.

<!-- Engineering Calculations -->
<h4 class="text-center mt-5">Engineering Calculations</h4>
<div class="text-center mt-2 mb-2">
  All calculations were performed manually and documented in a multi-tab Excel workbook 
  referencing ASHRAE 62.1 and IPC standards. Calculations include room-by-room airflow requirements using ACH methodology, duct sizing with velocity verification and outdoor air compliance. Key results include a total supply airflow 
  of 3,984 CFM for the training area and a building-wide outdoor air requirement of 
  1,034 CFM. Use the tabs below to navigate between calculation sheets.
</div>
